<p class="">I should like to start by thanking sincerely hon. and right hon. Gentlemen in all parts of the House for the way in which they have received the Navy Estimates. I desire to thank, first of all, my hon. Friend the Member for Windsor (Sir A. Somerville) for his short interruption, in case "Lord Haw Haw" ever got hold of the news that during the dinner hour in the House of <span id="2010" class="column-number" data-column-number="2010"></span> Commons a large number of Members, as is their wont, went out to dinner.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
